Once upon a time there was a little girl named Lily who lived in a small village at the foot of a mountain. One day while playing in the forest she discovered a tiny talking unicorn. The unicorn told her that she was the chosen one to save their kingdom from an evil sorcerer who lived on the top of the mountain. Despite her fear Lily bravely set off on her journey. Along the way she met many helpful creatures and learned the skills she needed to defeat the sorcerer and restore peace to the kingdom. And so she became known as the greatest hero the kingdom had ever seen.
No it's... everything. We think of human life as like a lantern that's lit one minute and extinguished the next but are we adepti so different? Perhaps as dust settles after a storm we too must one day return to the world below.
